rigger
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 2
Definition:orig. SQUARE-RIGGER, a square-gin bottle; thence any large flagon or demijohn for holding esp. draught beer. (or, Havelock, vinegar) cf PETER @n2


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (Jack Columbus 1980 Aug 25) ca1930's (Canterbury) for a square rigger; 40oz square green bottle of square (HJKZ) gin; also for stone jars, a gallon.
